Subject: [PATCH] clk: qcom: gcc-sm6115: Use retention for USB power domain

The USB subsystem does not expect to lose its state on suspend.

Based on: sc8180x by Val Packett in upstream commit 25bc96f26cd6.
Upstream-reference: clk: qcom: gcc-sc8180x: Use
                    retention for USB power domains
---
 drivers/clk/qcom/gcc-sm6115.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/clk/qcom/gcc-sm6115.c
+++ b/drivers/clk/qcom/gcc-sm6115.c
@@ -3210,7 +3210,7 @@
 	.pd = {
 		.name = "gcc_usb30_prim",
 	},
-	.pwrsts = PWRSTS_OFF_ON,
+	.pwrsts = PWRSTS_RET_ON,
 };
 
 static struct gdsc gcc_vcodec0_gdsc = {
